# API com autenticacao

## 1) Objetivo
Padronizar APIs ASP.NET Core MVC com autenticacao/autorizacao via JWT Bearer e observabilidade.

## 2) Estrutura de pastas
```
src/
  Api/
    Controllers/
    Filters/
    Program.cs
  Application/
    Services/
    DTOs/Validators/
  Domain/
    Entities/ValueObjects/
  Infrastructure/
    Identity/
    Data/Repositories/
    Observability/
deploy/
  Dockerfile
tests/
  Unit/
  Integration/
```

## 3) Pacotes recomendados
- Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer
- Serilog.AspNetCore, Serilog.Sinks.Console
- OpenTelemetry.Extensions.Hosting
- OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.AspNetCore, OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Http
- OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol
- MediatR
- FluentValidation
- Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore

## 4) Configuracao (Program.cs)
```csharp
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
builder.Host.UseSerilog((ctx, cfg) => cfg.ReadFrom.Configuration(ctx.Configuration));

builder.Services.AddAuthentication(JwtBearerDefaults.AuthenticationScheme)
    .AddJwtBearer(options =>
    {
        options.Authority = builder.Configuration["Auth:Authority"];
        options.Audience = builder.Configuration["Auth:Audience"];
        options.TokenValidationParameters.ValidateLifetime = true;
    });

builder.Services.AddAuthorization(opt =>
{
    opt.AddPolicy("api.read", p => p.RequireClaim("scope", "api.read"));
});

builder.Services.AddControllers(opt =>
{
    opt.Filters.Add<AuthorizeFilter>();
    opt.Filters.Add<CorrelationIdFilter>();
});

builder.Services.AddMediatR(cfg => cfg.RegisterServicesFromAssemblyContaining<Program>());
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t.AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation().AddHttpClientInstrumentation())
    .WithMetrics(m => m.AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation());

var app = builder.Build();
app.UseSerilogRequestLogging();
app.UseAuthentication();
app.UseAuthorization();
app.MapHealthChecks("/healthz");
app.MapControllers();
app.Run();
```

## 5) Exemplo de controller protegido
```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("api/orders")]
[Authorize(Policy = "api.read")]
public class OrdersController : ControllerBase
{
    [HttpGet]
    public IEnumerable<string> Get() => new[] { "order-1", "order-2" };
}
```

## 6) Observabilidade
- Logs estruturados com userId/tenant (sem dados sensiveis), traceId e correlation id.
- Traces e metrics via OpenTelemetry; exporter OTLP.
- Health checks expostos e protegidos conforme necessidade.

## 7) Testes
- Unit: services, handlers, validators, utilizar xunit/moq/fluentassertions.
- Integration: endpoints protegidos com JWT mockado via WebApplicationFactory.

## 8) Dockerfile (opcional)
```Dockerfile
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:9.0 AS base
WORKDIR /app

FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:9.0 AS build
WORKDIR /src
COPY . .
RUN dotnet restore ./src/Api/Api.csproj
RUN dotnet publish ./src/Api/Api.csproj -c Release -o /app/publish

FROM base AS final
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/publish .
ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "Api.dll"]
```

## 9) Checklist
- JWT Bearer configurado (authority/audience, policies).
- Observabilidade ativa (logs + traces + metrics + healthcheck).
- Testes unitarios e integracao cobrindo rotas protegidas.
